						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/70-top-African-women-agricultural-scientists-from-11-countries-chosen" title="70 top African women agricultural scientists from 11 countries chosen  " alt="link">70 top African women agricultural scientists from 11 countries chosen  </a></h2>

	
					<p>On 18 February 2015, <a href="http://www.awardfellowships.org/" target="_self">the African Women in Agricultural Research and Development</a>&nbsp;(AWARD) announced the winners of its 2015 fellowships: 70 top African women agricultural scientists from 11 African countries. AWARD fellowships are granted on the basis of each scientist’s intellectual merit, leadership capacity, and the potential of her work to improve the livelihoods of African smallholder farmers, most of whom are women. This year’s winners were selected from among an impressive cadre of 1109 applicants and will benefit from AWARD’s two-year career-development program that is focused on accelerating agricultural gains by strengthening their research and leadership skills. &nbsp; &nbsp;(AfricanBrains, 18/02/2015)<a href="http://www.apo-mail.org/150217aw" target="_self">Download</a> the list with the AWARD 2015 Fellowship Laureates</p>
