<h2><a class="listing" style="document" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/The-Ethics-of-Innovation-in-Agriculture-Inclusivity-and-Reflexivity" title="The Ethics of Innovation in Agriculture: Inclusivity and Reflexivity  " alt="document">The Ethics of Innovation in Agriculture: Inclusivity and Reflexivity  </a></h2>

	
	
	
	
					<p>By<b>&nbsp;Kristal Jones</b>, Research Associate, National Socio-Environmental Synthesis Center, University of Maryland, USA &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kristal Jones asks whose values and which ethics should drive innovation in agriculture and makes the case for an ethic of innovation in agricultural development that is built on the foundation of inclusivity and reflectivity.&nbsp;</p>
