						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="document" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Governance-of-science-technology-and-innovation-for-food-security-in-Africa-A-conceptual-framework-for-developing-indicators" title="Governance of science, technology and innovation for food security in Africa: A conceptual framework for developing indicators  " alt="document">Governance of science, technology and innovation for food security in Africa: A conceptual framework for developing indicators  </a></h2>

	
	
	
	
					<p>By<b>&nbsp;John Ouma-Mugabe, </b>Professor Science and Innovation Policy, University of Pretoria, South Africa &nbsp;&nbsp;John Mugabe believes that despite the increasing importance of the governance of science, technology and innovation, there are no conceptual tools or empirically tested indicators – quantitative or qualitative – to provide the evidence base given the complexity of science–technology–society interactions.&nbsp;</p>
							<p><span class="date">8/03/2015</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="document" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Governance-of-science-technology-and-innovation-for-food-security-in-Africa-A-conceptual-framework-for-developing-indicators">Read more...</a>
